org.melior.service.rabbitmq

Class RabbitMQListener<T>

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.melior.client.core.ClientConfig
      • org.melior.service.rabbitmq.RabbitMQListenerConfig
        • org.melior.service.rabbitmq.RabbitMQListener<T>

  • public class RabbitMQListener<T>
extends RabbitMQListenerConfig
    Implements an easy to use, auto-configuring RabbitMQ listener which listens to registered RabbitMQ queues and processes any new messages that arrive.

    If a queue is configured with a SingletonProcessor, then any new messages that arrive will be processed by the listener individually.

    The listener may be configured with multiple threads to speed up processing.

    Since:
    2.3
    Author:
    Melior
    See Also:
    RabbitMQQueue
